"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-xander-schauffele-targets-paris-2024-olympics-after-us-pga-championship-victory\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By:Frank Dalleres  Sports Editor  Xander Schauffele has set his sights on a successful defence of his Olympic title after winning a first major in record-breaking fashion at the US PGA Championship on Sunday.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xander_Schauffele\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xander Schauffele\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xander_Schauffele\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xander_Schauffele\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Schauffele holed a decisive birdie on the 18th hole to finish on 21 under par - the lowest score ever at a major - and pip fast-finishing Bryson DeChambeau by one shot.\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 496, \"end\": 506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryson_DeChambeau\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"DeChambeau\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryson_DeChambeau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryson_DeChambeau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It answered critics of his ability to close out tournaments and also delivered a timely boost just weeks ahead ofthe Paris 2024 Olympics, where he is set to represent Team USA.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 688, \"end\": 696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9055578011659369, \"rank\": 0.08477793368415815, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's just a cherry on top,\\\" said Schauffele, whose biggest career win saw himreplace Rory McIlroy as world No2.\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 811, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rory McIlroy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's totally separate to competing in the Olympics.\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The US team is a strong one.\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 870, \"end\": 872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.7763639248293085, \"rank\": 0.25075280711265735, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a hard one to qualify for.\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I imagine this win probably secures me into qualifying for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay in the game with The Turnover: your weekly roundup of sport business news, expert analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories from City\\u202fAM's sports desk.\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's a whole different ball game, winning that one, but I will definitely be able to pull some confidence from this thing.\\\"\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Success at the US PGA came days afterhis \\\"nearly man\\\" tagsurfaced again at the Wells Fargo Championship, where he was beaten by McIlroy on the final day.\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1299, \"end\": 1301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.7763639248293085, \"rank\": 0.25075280711265735, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A week later at Valhalla, former US Open champion DeChambeau threatened to take the 30-year-old to a play-off when he birdied the last to join him on 20 under par.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valhalla_Golf_Club\", \"score\": 0.9999999994508926, \"rank\": 5.49105404040093e-10, \"text\": \"Valhalla\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valhalla_Golf_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valhalla_Golf_Club\"}, {\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"score\": 0.935861658826044, \"rank\": 0.027464247762228403, \"text\": \"US Open\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\"}, {\"begin\": 1489, \"end\": 1499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryson_DeChambeau\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"DeChambeau\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryson_DeChambeau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryson_DeChambeau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Schauffele broke a run of five consecutive pars by holing from six feet - after an emotional pep talk from his dad - to complete a round of 65 and clinch a first win since July 2022.\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1790, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was actually able to call him when I was standing, waiting to walk onto the 18th green.\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was a mess.\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was crying on the phone,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It made me pretty emotional.\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I told him I had to hang up because I had to walk down.\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I could not show up looking the way I was.\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have become very patient not knocking off any wins in the last couple years.\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is awesome.\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's super sweet.\", \"from\": 2165, \"to\": 2182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All those close calls, even last week, that sort of feeling, it gets to you at some point.\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It just makes this even sweeter.\\\"\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World No5 Viktor Hovland took solo third on 18 under, three clear of one-time leader Collin Morikawa and Belgian Thomas Detry.\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2321, \"end\": 2335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Hovland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Viktor Hovland\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Hovland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Hovland\"}, {\"begin\": 2396, \"end\": 2411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Collin_Morikawa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Collin Morikawa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Collin_Morikawa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Collin_Morikawa\"}, {\"begin\": 2416, \"end\": 2423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9994869963893276, \"rank\": 0.0005116128665793253, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2424, \"end\": 2436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Detry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Detry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Detry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Detry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"England's Justin Rose and Ireland's Shane Lowry were a further shot back in sixth, one ahead of a group that included world No1 Scottie Scheffler and Scotland's Bob MacIntyre.\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2439, \"end\": 2446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7212792562036033, \"rank\": 0.3164892973952242, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2449, \"end\": 2460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Rose\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Justin Rose\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Rose\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Rose\"}, {\"begin\": 2465, \"end\": 2472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999216576466696, \"rank\": 3.910805972003118e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2475, \"end\": 2486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shane_Lowry_(golfer)\", \"score\": 0.9805012734846731, \"rank\": 0.019886363636360344, \"text\": \"Shane Lowry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shane_Lowry_(golfer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shane_Lowry_(golfer)\"}, {\"begin\": 2567, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scottie Scheffler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\"}, {\"begin\": 2589, \"end\": 2597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.992663253914098, \"rank\": 0.00739051372910619, \"text\": \"Scotland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2600, \"end\": 2603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"score\": 0.9862443822181518, \"rank\": 0.013939827459783642, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Share this article  Subscribe to the City AM newsletter to have our top stories delivered directly to your inbox.\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentenc